  "prompt": "Which are some Indian Fast-fashion Brands?",
  "response": "India has a number of fast-fashion brands that offer trendy and affordable clothing. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **FabAlley** - Known for its chic and fashionable clothing for women, FabAlley offers a wide range of apparel including dresses, tops, and accessories.\n\n2. **Bewakoof** - A popular brand among millennials, Bewakoof specializes in casual wear including t-shirts, joggers, and hoodies, often featuring quirky designs and slogans.\n\n3. **Masaba** - This brand blends traditional Indian prints and motifs with contemporary designs, offering a range of unique and trendy clothing options.\n\n4. **W for Woman** - W offers a mix of ethnic and contemporary styles, catering primarily to women looking for trendy yet affordable fashion.\n\n5. **Biba** - Although primarily known for ethnic wear, Biba also offers a range of contemporary styles that align with fast fashion trends.\n\n6. **Global Desi** - This brand captures the essence of Indian culture and turns it into fashionable, modern designs that appeal to young women.\n\n7. **AND** - A sister brand to Global Desi, AND focuses on Western wear, providing chic and modern clothing options for women.\n\n8. **Redefine** - A relatively new player in the market, Redefine offers trendy and affordable casual wear, often targeting the youth demographic.\n\n9. **Ajio** - Ajio, a part of Reliance Retail, is another prominent name offering a variety of fast fashion clothing including Western wear, ethnic wear, and accessories.\n\n10. **Pantaloons** - This brand provides a mix of Western and ethnic fashion at affordable prices, catering to a wide demographic.\n\nThese brands offer a variety of clothing options that cater to different tastes and preferences, making them popular choices in the fast-fashion segment in India.",
